[2026-03-19T10:00:25.735Z] [STDOUT] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Mn2NTF7Ewx7wsRanw3sbkD","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now let me compile a comprehensive report with all the findings:\n\n## Comprehensive Codebase Analysis for Metrics Query API Endpoints\n\nBased on my thorough exploration of the codebase, here are my complete findings for implementing metrics query API endpoints:\n\n### 1. SCHEMA DEFINITIONS (No metrics tables exist yet)\n\n**File:** `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/.claude/worktrees/radiant-twirling-map/packages/orchestrator/src/db.ts` (Lines 66-195)\n\nCurrently defined tables:\n- `personas` - persona configurations with project_id\n- `persona_events` - events with project_id and timestamps\n- `persona_executions` - execution records with detailed metrics:\n  - `input_tokens`, `output_tokens`, `cost_usd` (individual execution costs)\n  - `duration_ms`, `status` (queued, running, completed, failed, cancelled)\n  - `started_at`, `completed_at` timestamps\n  - `project_id` for multi-tenant isolation\n\n**Important:** The daily_metrics and system_daily_metrics tables **do not currently exist** and will need to be added to the SCHEMA constant.\n\n### 2. EXISTING API ROUTE PATTERNS\n\n**File:** `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/.claude/worktrees/radiant-twirling-map/packages/orchestrator/src/httpApi.ts` (Lines 1-616)\n\n**Route structure patterns:**\n- All routes use simple pathname matching: `if (pathname === '/api/...' && req.method === ...)`\n- Query parameters extracted via `new URLSearchParams(queryString || '')`\n- Route pattern: `/api/{resource}` for list/create, `/api/{resource}/{id}` for get/update/delete\n\n**Example query param handling (lines 200-209):**\n```typescript\nconst params = new URLSearchParams(queryString || '');\nconst events = db.listEvents(database, {\n  eventType: params.get('eventType') ?? undefined,\n  status: params.get('status') ?? undefined,\n  limit: params.get('limit') ? parseInt(params.get('limit')!, 10) : 50,\n  offset: params.get('offset') ? parseInt(params.get('offset')!, 10) : undefined,\n  projectId: scopedProjectId,\n});\n```\n\n### 3. AUTHENTICATION & AUTHORIZATION PATTERNS\n\n**File:** `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/.claude/worktrees/radiant-twirling-map/packages/orchestrator/src/auth.ts` (Lines 1-126)\n\n**Authentication mechanism:**\n- Dual auth: API key (Bearer token) + optional Supabase JWT in `x-user-token` header\n- All requests require API key validation (lines 70-76, 101-102)\n\n**RequestContext interface (lines 9-14):**\n```typescript\nexport interface RequestContext {\n  authType: 'user' | 'admin';\n  projectId: string;  // Supabase UUID for 'user', '__admin__' for admin\n  userEmail?: string;\n}\n```\n\n**Authorization logic in httpApi.ts (lines 44-52):**\n```typescript\nconst ctx = auth.validateAndExtractContext(req);\n// ...\nconst scopedProjectId = ctx.authType === 'admin' ? undefined : ctx.projectId;\n```\n\n**Admin endpoint pattern (lines 281-293):**\n```typescript\nelse if (pathname === '/api/admin/users' && req.method === 'GET' && database) {\n  if (requireAdmin(ctx, res)) return;  // Line 323-330: returns 403 if not admin\n  json(res, 200, { projectIds: db.listDistinctProjectIds(database) });\n}\n```\n\n### 4. DATABASE QUERY PATTERNS (better-sqlite3)\n\n**File:** `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/.claude/worktrees/radiant-twirling-map/packages/orchestrator/src/db.ts`\n\n**Query pattern for list operations with filtering (lines 657-687):**\n```typescript\nexport function listExecutions(db: Database.Database, opts?: {\n  personaId?: string; status?: string; limit?: number; offset?: number; projectId?: string;\n}): PersonaExecution[] {\n  let sql = 'SELECT * FROM persona_executions WHERE 1=1';\n  const params: unknown[] = [];\n\n  if (opts?.projectId) {\n    sql += ' AND project_id = ?';\n    params.push(opts.projectId);\n  }\n  // ... more conditions ...\n  sql += ' ORDER BY created_at DESC';\n  if (opts?.limit) {\n    sql += ' LIMIT ?';\n    params.push(opts.limit);\n  }\n  if (opts?.offset) {\n    sql += ' OFFSET ?';\n    params.push(opts.offset);\n  }\n  \n  const rows = db.prepare(sql).all(...params) as Record<string, unknown>[];\n  return rows.map(rowToExecution);\n}\n```\n\n**Key query patterns:**\n- Dynamic SQL construction with WHERE clauses (lines 499-504 in listEvents)\n- Parameterized queries to prevent SQL injection\n- Pagination support: `LIMIT` + `OFFSET` (lines 507, 681-682)\n- Ordering: `ORDER BY created_at DESC` (lines 507, 675)\n- Row mapping from SQL to TypeScript types (lines 257-325)\n\n**Default pagination:** 50 items per page (lines 505, 260)\n\n### 5. EXISTING METRICS-RELATED CODE\n\n**In persona_executions table (lines 171-192):**\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS persona_executions (\n  id TEXT PRIMARY KEY,\n  project_id TEXT NOT NULL,\n  persona_id TEXT NOT NULL,\n  -- ... other fields ...\n  input_tokens INTEGER DEFAULT 0,\n  output_tokens INTEGER DEFAULT 0,\n  cost_usd REAL DEFAULT 0,\n  duration_ms INTEGER,\n  status TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'queued',\n  started_at TEXT,\n  completed_at TEXT,\n  created_at TEXT NOT NULL\n);\nCREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_pex_persona ON persona_executions(persona_id);\nCreate INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_pex_status ON persona_executions(status);\n```\n\n**Types defined in shared package (lines 111-132 in types.ts):**\n```typescript\nexport interface PersonaExecution {\n  id: string;\n  projectId?: string;\n  personaId: string;\n  status: string;  // 'queued','running','completed','failed','cancelled'\n  inputTokens: number;\n  outputTokens: number;\n  costUsd: number;\n  durationMs: number | null;\n  startedAt: string | null;\n  completedAt: string | null;\n  createdAt: string;\n}\n```\n\n### 6. PROJECT STRUCTURE\n\n**Location:** `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/.claude/worktrees/radiant-twirling-map/`\n\n**Workspace structure (monorepo with npm workspaces):**\n- `packages/shared/` - Common types and utilities\n- `packages/orchestrator/` - HTTP API server (port 3001 via HTTP_PORT env var)\n- `packages/worker/` - Persona execution workers\n\n**Database:** SQLite with better-sqlite3 (uses WAL pragma on line 20)\n\n**Build setup:** TypeScript with strict mode, NodeNext module resolution\n\n### IMPLEMENTATION RECOMMENDATIONS\n\nFor adding metrics query endpoints, you should:\n\n1. **Add schema tables** to the SCHEMA constant in db.ts for:\n   - `daily_metrics` table with date-based bucketing\n   - `system_daily_metrics` table for system-wide aggregates\n\n2. **Follow existing patterns:**\n   - Add typed database functions in db.ts (like `listExecutions`)\n   - Implement row mapping functions (like `rowToExecution`)\n   - Support project_id filtering for multi-tenancy\n   - Add pagination with limit/offset defaults of 50\n\n3. **HTTP endpoint structure:**\n   - Regular endpoint: `/api/metrics` (user scoped to their project)\n   - Admin endpoint: `/api/admin/metrics` (all projects)\n   - Use `scopedProjectId` pattern for automatic tenant isolation\n\n4. **Query parameter patterns:**\n   - `?startDate=YYYY-MM-DD`\n   - `?endDate=YYYY-MM-DD`\n   - `?limit=100&offset=0`\n   - `?personaId=xxx` (for filtered metrics)\n   - Support optional filters like `?status=completed`\n\nAll files are absolute paths and ready for implementation. The codebase uses standard Express-less Node.js http module patterns with better-sqlite3 for ORM-like operations."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: ad2267a708a103755 (use SendMessage with to: 'ad2267a708a103755' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 53914\ntool_uses: 35\nduration_ms: 92434</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7333e80d-4ed0-46b0-8f92-568f2de6df25","uuid":"f99213be-9d3f-4248-b2c5-31b32eca5e2e","timestamp":"2026-03-19T10:00:25.650Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"I need to understand the codebase structure for implementing metrics query API endpoints. 